[size=4][b]BetterBots — Smarter Solo Play Bots for Darktide[/b][/size]

BetterBots makes Solo Play bots act more like real teammates.

They use combat abilities, throw grenades and blitzes, protect revives, ping threats, carry books, manage ammo more sensibly, and generally stop feeling like dead weight.

[b]Solo Play only.[/b] Darktide uses dedicated servers, so gameplay mods only work when you host locally through [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/176]Solo Play[/url]. This mod does [b]not[/b] affect public matchmaking.

[size=3][b]Why use this mod?[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Bots actually use their career abilities instead of sitting on them all mission
[*]Grenades and blitzes are supported across all classes
[*]Bots help more with revives, pressure, poxbursters, and priority targets
[*]Ammo, healing, and pickup behavior is less selfish
[*]Class-diverse bot profiles give you more than four copy-pasted veterans
[/list]

[size=3][b]New in v0.11.0 — Combat Execution[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Better grenade throws:[/b] gravity-affected grenades now aim like actual projectiles instead of lobbing at bad flat angles
[*][b]Book mules:[/b] bots can carry scriptures and tomes; grimoires stay optional behind a setting
[*][b]Better stream weapons:[/b] flamers, Purgatus, heavy stubbers, recon/autoguns, autopistols, bolter hipfire, and ripperguns now follow the correct fire path more reliably
[*][b]More natural bot timing:[/b] human-likeness timing and pressure profiles now default to sensible [i]auto[/i] behavior based on difficulty
[*][b]Steadier targeting:[/b] bots swap less erratically between melee and ranged priorities
[*][b]Cleaner pickups:[/b] ammo handling is more reliable again, and grenade refill support is in
[/list]

[size=3][b]What bots can use[/b][/size]

[b]Combat abilities[/b]
[list]
[*]Veteran: Executioner's Stance, Voice of Command, Infiltrate
[*]Zealot: Fury of the Faithful, Shroudfield, relic
[*]Psyker: Scrier's Gaze, Venting Shriek, Telekine Shield
[*]Ogryn: Point-Blank Barrage, Bull Rush, Loyal Protector
[*]Arbites: Castigator's Stance, Break the Line, Nuncio-Aquila, whistle, shock mine
[/list]

[b]Grenades and blitzes[/b]
[list]
[*]Frag, krak, smoke, fire, shock, cluster, rock, flash, tox
[*]Zealot Throwing Knives
[*]Psyker Assail, Smite, Chain Lightning
[*]Arbites whistle and shock mine
[*]Hive Scum missile launcher support is included, but still needs DLC-side validation
[/list]

[size=3][b]What bots do better[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Use abilities when a fight actually calls for them
[*]Pop defensive abilities before reviving downed allies
[*]Stagger team cooldowns instead of dumping everything at once
[*]Protect allies doing objectives and pickups
[*]Ping elites and specials for the player
[*]Avoid wasteful poxburster shots and push when needed
[*]Stay engaged in fights longer without wandering off uselessly
[*]Use smarter melee attacks into hordes and armor
[*]Carry scriptures and tomes for the team
[*]Defer healing and ammo more intelligently to human players
[*]Steer the Arbites mastiff onto better targets
[/list]

[size=3][b]Settings you can control[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Aggression preset: Testing / Aggressive / Balanced / Conservative
[*]Toggle ability groups on or off: stances, charges, shouts, stealth, deployables, grenades
[*]Sprint distance, chase range, player-tag response, and melee horde bias sliders
[*]Smart blitz targeting toggle
[*]Daemonhost avoidance toggle
[*]Poxburster safety toggle
[*]Ammo reserve thresholds for bots and humans
[*]Human-likeness timing and pressure profiles
[*]Healing deferral options
[*]Bot grimoire pickup toggle
[*]Bot profile class selection and weapon quality
[*]Debug level, JSONL event log, and `/bb_perf` diagnostics
[/list]

[size=3][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/19]Darktide Mod Loader[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/8]Darktide Mod Framework (DMF)[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/176]Solo Play[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/183]Tertium 5[/url] or [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/725]Tertium 6[/url] if you want class-diverse bots based on player profiles
[/list]

[b]Note:[/b] If Tertium 5 crashes with newer classes like Arbites or Hive Scum, switch to [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/725]Tertium 6[/url].

[size=3][b]Install[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Extract [font=Courier New]BetterBots.zip[/font] into your Darktide [font=Courier New]mods/[/font] folder
[*]Add [font=Courier New]BetterBots[/font] to [font=Courier New]mods/mod_load_order.txt[/font] below [font=Courier New]dmf[/font]
[*]Re-patch mods
[/list]

[size=3][b]Quick check[/b][/size]

Start a Solo Play mission and look for [font=Courier New]BetterBots loaded[/font] in chat.

[size=3][b]Known issues[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Daemonhost avoidance has improved, but it is still being watched after reports of rare edge cases with dormant daemonhosts
[*]Mods are disabled after every Darktide update, so you will need to re-patch
[*]Hive Scum ability support is still partly untested unless you own that DLC
[*]Some item-style abilities still rely on template-specific handling, so future game patches can occasionally break a path until it is updated
[/list]

[size=3][b]Planned next[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Better weapon-aware ADS vs hip-fire behavior
[*]Healing item management
[*]Weapon special actions like parry/bayonet
[/list]

